02/06/2003
TIRANA, Albania -- Russian companies are interested in investing in Albania's oil and power sectors, according to Russian Deputy Finance Minister Aleksei Ulyukayev, who visited Tirana on Sunday (1 June).
Talking to Economy Minister Arben Malaj, Ulyukayev said that prominent Russian companies would like to explore unspecified investment opportunities in Albania's energy sector, as well as in infrastructure projects, especially road reconstruction.
(ATA, BBC - 01/06/03)
